01
Launch EC2 instance
Start an Ubuntu EC2 instance and connect via SSH using your key pair.
02
Install dependencies
Update apt and install Python, pip, MySQL client, and any required build tools.
03
Create virtual environment
Inside your project folder run `python3 -m venv venv` and activate it with `source venv/bin/activate`.
04
Install Django and MySQL client
Run `pip install django mysqlclient` to set up the framework and database connector.
05
Configure database settings
Edit `settings.py` to point to your RDS endpoint, username, password, and port 3306.
06
Run migrations cleanly
Execute `python manage.py migrate` to let Django create all required tables in MySQL.
07
Create superuser
Run `python manage.py createsuperuser` to set up an admin account for the Django admin panel.
08
Run server on EC2
Start with `python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000` so it listens on all interfaces.
09
Open EC2 security group
Add inbound rule for TCP port 8000 to allow external access from your IP or 0.0.0.0/0 for testing.
10
Update ALLOWED_HOSTS
In `settings.py` add your EC2 public IP or DNS name to `ALLOWED_HOSTS` to avoid DisallowedHost errors.
11
Access Django app
Visit `http://<EC2-IP>:8000/` in your browser and log in with your superuser credentials.
